        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 4:49PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Pine Apple, or 16 miles west of Greenville, moving
east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pine Apple.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
